.TH DP_STREAM_EVENT 3 "March 13, 2026" "libdisasterparty @DP_VERSION@" "Disaster Party Manual"

.SH NAME
dp_stream_event_t \- structure for detailed streaming events

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include <disasterparty.h>
.PP
.nf
typedef struct {
    dp_stream_event_type_t event_type;
    const char* raw_json_data;
} dp_stream_event_t;

typedef enum {
    DP_EVENT_UNKNOWN,
    DP_EVENT_MESSAGE_START,
    DP_EVENT_CONTENT_BLOCK_START,
    DP_EVENT_PING,
    DP_EVENT_CONTENT_BLOCK_DELTA,
    DP_EVENT_CONTENT_BLOCK_STOP,
    DP_EVENT_MESSAGE_DELTA,
    DP_EVENT_MESSAGE_STOP,
    DP_EVENT_ERROR,
    DP_EVENT_THINKING_DELTA
} dp_stream_event_type_t;
.fi

.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B dp_stream_event_t
structure is used by
.BR dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion (3).
It provides fine-grained information about the state of an LLM stream across different providers.

.SH MEMBERS
.TP
.B event_type
Identifies the nature of the event (e.g., text delta, reasoning delta, or stream end).
.TP
.B raw_json_data
The underlying JSON payload for the event.

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR dp_perform_detailed_streaming_completion (3),
.BR disasterparty (7)
